.TH FLOWCOIN-TX "1" "March 2026" "FlowCoin Core 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
flowcoin\-tx \- FlowCoin offline transaction utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B flowcoin\-tx
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIPARAMS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Offline transaction creation and manipulation utility for FlowCoin.
Creates, inspects, and signs transactions without requiring a running
\fBflowcoind\fR(1) daemon or network connectivity.
.PP
Useful for cold storage, hardware wallet integration, and offline
transaction signing workflows.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-create\fR
Create a new raw transaction.
.TP
\fB\-json\fR
Output results as JSON.
.TP
\fB\-txid\fR
Output only the transaction ID (hash).
.TP
\fB\-testnet\fR
Use testnet address format (HRP: \fItfl\fR).
.TP
\fB\-regtest\fR
Use regtest address format (HRP: \fIflrt\fR).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBin=\fR\fItxid:vout\fR
Add a transaction input. May be specified multiple times.
.TP
\fBout=\fR\fIaddress:amount\fR
Add a transaction output. May be specified multiple times.
.TP
\fBsign=\fR\fIprivkey_hex\fR
Sign all inputs with the given Ed25519 private key (hex format).
.TP
\fBset=\fR\fIkey:value\fR
Set a transaction field (version, locktime).
.TP
\fBdecode\fR
Decode a raw transaction (hex) and print its contents.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Create a transaction
flowcoin\-tx \-create in=abc123:0 out=fl1q...:1.5 out=fl1q...:3.2

# Decode a raw transaction
flowcoin\-tx decode 0100000001...

# Sign a transaction
flowcoin\-tx sign=abcdef... < unsigned.hex
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR flowcoind (1),
.BR flowcoin\-cli (1)
